column3: ```ttl@prefix : <http://example.org/time#> .@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .:TemporalEntity rdf:type rdfs:Class .:Instant rdf:type rdfs:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TemporalEntity .:Interval rdf:type rdfs:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TemporalEntity .:Time rdf:type rdfs:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TemporalEntity .:hasBeginning rdf:type rdf:Property ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range :Instant .:hasEnd rdf:type rdf:Property ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range :Instant .:hasDuration rdf:type rdf:Property ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range xsd:duration .:instantInInterval rdf:type rdf:Property ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Interval .:hasTime rdf:type rdf:Property ;    rdfs:domain :TemporalEntity ;    rdfs:range :Time .:isBefore rdf:type rdf:Property ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Instant .:isAfter rdf:type rdf:Property ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Instant .:Interval rdfs:comment "A time interval is a connected temporal entity of non-zero duration" .:Instant rdfs:comment "A point in time with zero duration" .:Time rdfs:comment "A general temporal entity, which can be an instant or an interval" .```

column2: Design an ontology to encompass the following: time.   Provide it in valid Turtle/RDF format, excluding any extra text.
column3: ```turtle@prefix : <http://example.org/time#> .@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .:TemporalEntity a owl:Class ;    rdfs:label "Temporal Entity" ;    rdfs:comment "A superclass for all entities related to time." .:Instant a owl:Class ;    rdfs:label "Instant" ;    rdfs:comment "A specific point in time, an exact time instant." ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TemporalEntity .:Interval a owl:Class ;    rdfs:label "Interval" ;    rdfs:comment "A duration of time, defined by a start and an end instant." ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TemporalEntity .:StartInstant a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:label "start instant" ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:comment "The instant at which an interval starts." .:EndInstant a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:label "end instant" ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:comment "The instant at which an interval ends." .:hasDuration a owl:DatatypeProperty ;    rdfs:label "has duration" ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range xsd:duration ;    rdfs:comment "The duration of a temporal interval." .:before a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:label "before" ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:comment "Indicates that one instant is before another." .:after a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:label "after" ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:comment "Indicates that one instant is after another." .:overlaps a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:label "overlaps" ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range :Interval ;    rdfs:comment "Indicates that two intervals have some time in common." .:TemporalEntity rdf:type owl:Thing .```

column2: Formulate an ontology related to time. Provide it in valid Turtle/RDF format, excluding any extra text.
column3: ```turtle@prefix : <http://example.org/time#> .@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .:TimeConcept a owl:Class ;    rdfs:label "Time Concept" ;    rdfs:comment "A general concept representing time-related entities." .:Instant a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TimeConcept ;    rdfs:label "Instant" ;    rdfs:comment "A specific point in time." .:Interval a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TimeConcept ;    rdfs:label "Interval" ;    rdfs:comment "A duration between two instants." .:hasBeginning a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:label "has beginning" ;    rdfs:comment "Associates an interval with its starting instant." .:hasEnding a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:label "has ending" ;    rdfs:comment "Associates an interval with its ending instant." .:before a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:label "before" ;    rdfs:comment "Indicates that one instant is before another." .:after a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:label "after" ;    rdfs:comment "Indicates that one instant is after another." .:duration a owl:DatatypeProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range xsd:duration ;    rdfs:label "duration" ;    rdfs:comment "Specifies the duration of a time interval." .:Year a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :Interval ;    rdfs:label "Year" ;    rdfs:comment "A time interval lasting approximately 365 days." .:Month a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :Interval ;    rdfs:label "Month" ;    rdfs:comment "A time interval lasting approximately 30 days." .:Day a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :Interval ;    rdfs:label "Day" ;    rdfs:comment "A time interval lasting 24 hours." .```

column2: Design an ontology to encompass the following: time.   Provide it in valid Turtle/RDF format, excluding any extra text.
column3: ```turtle@prefix : <http://example.org/time#> .@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .:TimeEntity rdf:type rdfs:Class ;    rdfs:label "Time Entity" ;    rdfs:comment "A general concept for any representation of time." .:Instant rdf:type rdfs:Class ;    rdfs:label "Instant" ;    rdfs:comment "A specific point in time." ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TimeEntity .:Interval rdf:type rdfs:Class ;    rdfs:label "Interval" ;    rdfs:comment "A duration between two time instants." ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TimeEntity .:hasStart rdf:type rdf:Property ;    rdfs:label "has start" ;    rdfs:comment "Relates an interval to its starting instant." ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range :Instant .:hasEnd rdf:type rdf:Property ;    rdfs:label "has end" ;    rdfs:comment "Relates an interval to its ending instant." ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range :Instant .:hasDuration rdf:type rdf:Property ;    rdfs:label "has duration" ;    rdfs:comment "Relates an interval to its duration." ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range xsd:duration .:TemporalUnit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;    rdfs:label "Temporal Unit" ;    rdfs:comment "Units of time measurement, such as seconds, minutes, hours." .:second rdf:type :TemporalUnit ;    rdfs:label "Second" .:minute rdf:type :TemporalUnit ;    rdfs:label "Minute" .:hour rdf:type :TemporalUnit ;    rdfs:label "Hour" .:date rdf:type rdf:Property ;    rdfs:label "date" ;    rdfs:comment "A property representing a calendar date." ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range xsd:date .:time rdf:type rdf:Property ;    rdfs:label "time" ;    rdfs:comment "A property representing a specific time of the day." ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range xsd:time .:occurs rdf:type rdf:Property ;    rdfs:label "occurs" ;    rdfs:comment "Relates an event or occurrence to a specific time entity." ;    rdfs:range :TimeEntity .```

column2: Formulate an ontology related to time. Provide it in valid Turtle/RDF format, excluding any extra text.
column3: ```turtle@prefix : <http://example.org/time#> .@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .:TimeEntity a owl:Class .:Instant a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TimeEntity .:Interval a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TimeEntity ;    owl:equivalentClass [        a owl:Class ;        owl:intersectionOf (            [ a owl:Restriction ;              owl:onProperty :hasStart ;              owl:someValuesFrom :Instant            ]            [ a owl:Restriction ;              owl:onProperty :hasEnd ;              owl:someValuesFrom :Instant            ]        )    ] .:hasStart a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range :Instant .:hasEnd a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range :Instant .:Duration a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TimeEntity .:hasDuration a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Interval ;    rdfs:range :Duration .:TemporalUnit a owl:Class .:Second a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TemporalUnit .:Minute a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TemporalUnit .:Hour a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TemporalUnit .:Day a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TemporalUnit .:Month a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TemporalUnit .:Year a owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :TemporalUnit .:hasTemporalUnit a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Duration ;    rdfs:range :TemporalUnit .:TemporalRelation a owl:ObjectProperty .:before a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:subPropertyOf :TemporalRelation ;    owl:inverseOf :after ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Instant .:after a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:subPropertyOf :TemporalRelation ;    owl:inverseOf :before ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Instant .:during a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:subPropertyOf :TemporalRelation ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Interval .:equals a owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:subPropertyOf :TemporalRelation ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Instant .```

column2: Design an ontology to encompass the following: time.   Provide it in valid Turtle/RDF format, excluding any extra text.
column3: ```turtle@prefix : <http://example.org/time#> .@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .:Time rdf:type owl:Class ;    rdfs:label "Time" ;    rdfs:comment "A temporal concept representing a point or duration in the continuum of existence." .:Instant rdf:type owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :Time ;    rdfs:label "Instant" ;    rdfs:comment "A precise point in time without duration." .:Duration rdf:type owl:Class ;    rdfs:subClassOf :Time ;    rdfs:label "Duration" ;    rdfs:comment "A span of time with a measurable length." .:hasBeginning rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Duration ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:label "has beginning" ;    rdfs:comment "Relates a duration to its starting point in time." .:hasEnd rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Duration ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:label "has end" ;    rdfs:comment "Relates a duration to its ending point in time." .:hasDuration rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Duration ;    rdfs:range xsd:duration ;    rdfs:label "has duration" ;    rdfs:comment "Specifies the length of a duration." .:occursAt rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Thing ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:label "occurs at" ;    rdfs:comment "Associates an event or occurrence with a specific instant in time." .:before rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:label "before" ;    rdfs:comment "Indicates temporal precedence between two instants." .:after rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:label "after" ;    rdfs:comment "Indicates temporal succession between two instants." .:contains rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Duration ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:label "contains" ;    rdfs:comment "Specifies that an instant is within the span of a duration." .:sameAs rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;    rdfs:domain :Instant ;    rdfs:range :Instant ;    rdfs:label "same as" ;    rdfs:comment "Indicates temporal equality between two instants." .```
